The paper discusses the use of honeypots for security purposes, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the organization and development of honeypot systems, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE). The use of honeypots for detecting and deflecting unauthorized accesses involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) and system integration (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the classification and taxonomy of honeypot techniques, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
